## Problem

Background-job agents currently self-signal completion by emitting `result:` on its own line. The harness classifier reads that line and flips the job to "completed" in the job list — silently, without Nick's review. Nick wants every background agent to pause for human approval at the end of its work instead, so nothing leaves the system marked done unless he explicitly confirms it.

The signal vocabulary itself (`result:`, `needs input:`, `failed:`) is harness-injected into the background-session prompt and is already a classifier-side text extraction. So overriding the rule is an instruction change, not a code change: a constitutional directive that tells the agent to always write `needs input:` (asking Nick to confirm completion) instead of `result:`.

## Vision

Every Jarvis-spawned background job ends in a clean handshake: the agent writes a one-line `needs input: ready for your review — confirm complete?` and waits. Nick scans the job list, opens anything interesting, replies "yes" to clear it. No background work ever marks itself done. The behavior is constitutional (survives compaction) and scoped to background sessions only — live conversations keep working as they do today.

## Out of Scope

- Modifying the Claude Code harness itself or the classifier code — this is a doctrine change, not a binary patch.
- Foreground/live conversations — they keep their current completion semantics.
- The `failed:` signal — structural failures should still surface as failed, not needs-input.
- Subagent behaviour inside a background session — subagents follow the primary's mode regardless.
- A new hook to enforce this dynamically — option (a) is the simpler directive-only path Nick approved.
- Job-list UI changes — the job list already renders needs-input distinctly.

## Constraints

- The rule lives in `PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` so it survives compaction (constitutional layer).
- The rule must be scoped to background sessions (the prompt's "# Background Session" context) and must NOT apply to live conversations.
- Must not break the `failed:` signal — genuine structural failures still emit `failed:`.
- Must not break the MINIMAL/NATIVE/ALGORITHM output-format mandates — the `needs input:` line is a *signal*, written inside the chosen format's final field, not freeform prose outside it.
- Markdown-only, no XML/HTML tags in the directive text.

## Goal

Add a constitutional directive to `PAI_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` that, in background sessions only, forbids `result:` and mandates `needs input: <one-line summary + confirm-complete ask>` as the closing signal — so every background job pauses for Nick's approval before it can move to completed.

